headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 29 points, Jarrett Allen had 16 points and 10 rebounds, and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Memphis Grizzlies 110-98 on Wednesday night to move within a victory of wrapping up a playoff spot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 29 points, Cavaliers beat Grizzlies 110-98 to close in on playoff berth

headlines.description: — Miles Bridges made a layup with 3.8 seconds left and the Charlotte Hornets beat Atlanta 115-114 on Wednesday night to spoil Hawks star Trae Young's return from a finger injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets spoil Young's return, beating Hawks 115-114 on Bridges' late layup

headlines.description: — Cam Thomas had 23 points, Dennis Schroder scored 15 of his 21 points in the fourth quarter and the Brooklyn Nets rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 106-102 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Thomas scores 23 points, Nets rally to beat Raptors 106-102 in home finale

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving clinched a $1 million bonus. Luka Doncic nearly got another triple-double. Daniel Gafford's latest can't-miss streak continued.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 29, Irving adds 25 and Mavericks roll past Heat 111-92 to claim Southwest Division

headlines.description: — Bobby Portis had 30 points, nine rebounds and a career-high five steals to help the Milwaukee Bucks withstand Giannis Antetokounmpo's absence and beat the Orlando Magic 117-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portis scores 30 points, Bucks beat Magic 117-99 without injured Antetokounmpo

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Thunder coach Mark Daigneault has preached all season that his team is about the process rather than results.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 26 as Thunder roll past Wembanyama-less Spurs, 127-89

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic minimized the matchup between teams tied atop the Western Conference standings, then put on a show for the ages — and for anyone still doubting he's the best player on the planet.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 41 points and leads Nuggets past Timberwolves 116-107 to take lead in West
Suns rally in 4th to beat Clippers 124-108 to split home-and-home set after blowout loss
